AS IF raping his victims wasn&rsquo;t evil enough, alleged serial rapist Joseph Mahloma (28) reportedly forced some of them to wash themselves in sewage water!These chilling details were contained in the indictment of Joseph from Ebony Park kasi, Ekurhuleni.He is facing a total of 104 charges, including 22 counts of rape, 17 of kidnapping and 17 of robbery.He has pleaded not guilty. His alleged reign of terror started in January 2011 and only came to an end in 2014 when he was arrested. His youngest victim was a 14-year-old girl. He appeared in the South Gauteng High Court yesterday. His accomplice &ndash; who is still on the run &ndash; allegedly used a gun and steel pipe to subdue the women before raping them. The trial continues.